<subSubSection id="7C591D34086E391F250E66606D96399E" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" type="comments">
<paragraph id="CE5D993D088C283EF2BD64B0CB390E20" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A961CC9B7D878FD837F078666EB89FC8" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName id="10FFCD39E97A78A88AEEFB5737FC0602" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia viridifrons" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridifrons">
<emphasis id="A8515A43CBF323C3FE955C3F4B5CAFE6" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia viridifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not listed as occurring in NB or Canada by 
<bibRefCitation id="6C939F7462746BAC9D7620EDE4229039" author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="109, Sofia-Moscow" pageId="65" pageNumber="330" refId="B6" refString="Bousquet, Y, Bouchard, P, Davies, AE, Sikes, D, 2013. Checklist of beetles (Coleoptera) of Canada and Alaska. Pensoft Series Faunistica No. 109, Sofia-Moscow" title="Checklist of beetles (Coleoptera) of Canada and Alaska. Pensoft Series Faunistica No." year="2013">Bousquet et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="317C5A67F9B69258E33DB45B4CA400D5" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia viridifrons" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridifrons">
<emphasis id="F2E7D58F8A13607A3B04875C3B37BB51" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia viridifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4AAEC7795670478D67418CE2FF0E176A" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia viridicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridicornis">
<emphasis id="FA86F44585E2A059F17883B71067E3C6" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia viridicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Say) were treated as distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation id="52A44D79D8F3D47F2B767DB04D1ECF54" author="MacRae, TC" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="66" pageNumber="331" pagination="166 - 199" refId="B26" refString="MacRae, TC, 2006. Distributional and biological records of North American Buprestidae (Coleoptera), with comments on variation in Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) cyanella Gory and A. (H.) viridifrons Gory. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 82: 166 - 199" title="Distributional and biological records of North American Buprestidae (Coleoptera), with comments on variation in Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) cyanella Gory and A. (H.) viridifrons Gory." volume="82" year="2006">MacRae (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, who noted that some Canadian records of 
<taxonomicName id="AC61A8EE7D84EA89A484E709C3E0A6AC" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia virdicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virdicornis">
<emphasis id="0CC9388B71FC181A534C0F6D73219826" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia virdicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might pertain to 
<taxonomicName id="C42FC64A832DB1C4C335BBFF1D7E4199" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia viridifrons" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridifrons">
<emphasis id="A7E3954B7669D7A10CB7EE15098678B2" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia viridifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="FEFA4F6481B0540BBB86D34B0F2D7CF0" author="Paiero, SM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Food Inspection Agency" pageId="67" pageNumber="332" refId="B41" refString="Paiero, SM, Jackson, MD, Jewiss-Gaines, A, Kimoto, T, Gill, BD, Marshall, SA, 2012. Field Guide to the Jewel Beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) of Northeastern North America. Canadian Food Inspection Agency" title="Field Guide to the Jewel Beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) of Northeastern North America" year="2012">Paiero et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
followed this treatment and reported 
<taxonomicName id="DCB0AA1C2311F2ECCF0EDF05D2D29F9C" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthaxia viridifrons" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridifrons">
<emphasis id="9AB3DA522EFF467516DB594A4BBC31D9" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Anthaxia viridifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from MB, ON, and QC.
</paragraph>
